Estimates of price elasticities of demand for selected markets (fashion store sales channels) on country+config_sku level. The estimates are calculated based on 12 months of historical data and updated on a monthly basis (only the latest values are available).
 
This maps the latest elasticity estimates to products contained in dwh_insider.d_article_config. This is the go-to solution for almost all users. It removes outlier estimates and fills in missing values with reasonable fallbacks.
 
The historical raw elasticity estimates are stored internally and not made public. These values are calculated for different commodity group and brand combinations where some brands/commodity groups have been clustered. Because of this, extra care needs to be taken when mapping the estimates to products. This is what the morpheus_config_elasticity table is for.
 
Note: This table only provides the latest config-market level elasticity ( using the latest morpheus_elasticity_raw and d_article_config tables ). For more info check out the script
 

Mirrodin: we publish Mirrodin signal for the dataset creation under `horizon` group. Sample Mirrodin payload

  "mirrodin_payload": {
    "group": "horizon",
    "artifact": "config_price_elasticity",
    "version": "2023-05-08"
  }

Offers of Zalando for a specific product (Simple SKU, “Merchandise”, “Articles”) to our customers are crucial for steering business decisions, but also quite complex due to our evolving business model. 

Curated Product Offer Data, in fact, in order to be complete must carry information about the products themselves, the merchants who are offering them, the sales channels through which they are sold as well as of course, the monetary information regarding the value ("price") of the offer. 

The business value of this data can support a wide range of cases, from real-time monitoring of the prices e.g. during cyber week, to follow "hot drops" during the day, to longer-term analysis on the shelf life cycle of a product or a group of products.

Further Documentation: https://curated-product-data.docs.zalando.net/products/offers/

curated_salesorder_address_data_daily (in short, called CSOAD Daily) is a daily updated data offering that can be used to retrieve the shipping and billing addresses linked with all sales orders placed until midnight (CET/CEST Berlin Time) of the previous solar day.
The dataset contains the full history of the addresses information for all the order history dating back to 2008, and has full retention (older orders are not deleted).

This dataset is built based on the Nakadi source event: sales-order-service.order-placed.v2 

The dataset also contains the basic identifiers needed for interoperability, like the order_number, customer_number, etc.

The dataset also includes beauty samples, gift cards (physical as well as digital), plus subscriptions and test orders.

The dataset includes sensitive information such as billing and shipping addresses. As a result, accessing this information requires a DPR (Data Processing Request). However, there is an insider version available under the zalando_data_products_insider schema, which excludes these sensitive details and can be queried without the need for a DPR.

Owner: Curated Sales Data || curated-sales-data@zalando.de || Public chat
